rows.titleText: Just moments ago, you were in your bed, peacefully falling asleep. The next moment, you are in a sea of stars, impossibly floating amongst the emptiness of space. Is this a dream? No, it feels far too real. And yet the situation is far too surreal to be anything but a dream. Ah, you're awake. Good. Before we begin, let's get the simple things out of the way, shall we? No, this is not a dream. Yes, this is very much real. I am Professor Paradox. The same one from the television show you call 'Ben 10,' yet not at the same time. And yes, Ben Tennyson is also real. Does that cover everything? You look around, still stunned by the fact that you're somehow floating in space and not dead. Ah, right! You're likely wondering where you are right now. We are in the space between universes right now. Don't worry about air, you don't need it, at least, not at this moment. My gauntlet emits a steady stream of breathable air at all times just for situations like this. Now, as for why you're here. We've recently discovered that the Omniverse is but a fraction of that reality. There are multiple Omniverses, each with their own rules and logic, and each needs to be defended. Tennyson and his allies have been defending our Omniverse for some time, but yours and the others are currently unguarded. That's where you come in. We've selected you and a number of other individuals from your universe to join our new defense force. Naturally, you can decline, but it's unlikely you'll receive another chance like this in your lifetime. If you accept, you'll be allowed to enroll as a member of the Plumbers and be given your own #trix, an upgraded version of the Omnitrix. We'll discuss the details of that later. As a bonus, we'll also use our technology to grant you a new body of your choice. Additionally, you can either choose which universe you will initially defend, many of which will be quite similar to those you would find in the works of fiction of your universe. So, what say you? Do you dare to enter the Ultraverse?

That's a shame... In that case, I'll return you to your life on Earth with no memories of our meeting. Alas, your planet isn't ready for the information I've given you. Perhaps in a few hundred years. You can still change your mind, however. If you don't change your mind, it isn't long before you're back in your bed, having no recollection of what just happened. You should be able to live the rest of your days in peace... hopefully?
Splendid. In that case, let's begin, shall we? There are many choices to be made.

rows.title: Physical Traits
rows.titleText: To begin with, let's decide on your physical state. I'm of course referring to your body. We have the technology to transform you into the ideal form of your choice, and it's worth mentioning that the Neotrix will constantly keep you in your prime so long as you don't disable the feature. I'll let you decide the details such as hair and eye color on your own... Yes, you can pick more fantastic ones such as purple or pink. We'll also allow you to pick any gender you wish. That includes those that don't fit into the binary. The Plumbers don't judge.

rows.title: Species
rows.titleText: To clarify, this is your species when the Neotrix is not active. In other words, your base form. For Tennyson, this was and still is human. I expect most of our new members to choose the same. Before you ask, no, you cannot be a Celestialsapian or a To'kustar. Such a thing would be ridiculous.

objects.title: Human
objects.text: You know humans well. They're native to your homeworld, Earth, as well as many planets and universes throughout the Ultraverse. They're largely unremarkable, but it would be the simplest and least drastic option. A solid choice that would result in little adjustment.

objects.title: Osmosian
objects.text: Osmosians are humans with unique genetic components in their DNA. This notably grants each Osmosian a different and unique ability. This can range from energy and material absorption to technokinesis to insect control. Essentially, Osmosian is the correct term to describe a 'mutant.'

objects.title: Half-Anodite
objects.text: You'll be an Anodite, or a half-Anodite to be more specific. Anodites are energy beings from Anodyne capable of manipulating manna to create energy constructs and cast magic spells. You cannot be a full Anodite, unfortunately. They cannot bond with a Neotrix, under normal conditions.

objects.title: Revonnahgander
objects.text: Revonnahganders are aliens from Revonnah. They possess various feline-like abilities, from enhanced strength and flexibility to heightened reflexes. They've been close allies of the Plumbers for some time now thanks to the efforts of one Rook Blonko.

objects.title: Appoplexian
objects.text: Appoplexians are... unruly beasts, to say the least. They're cat-like aliens from the planet of Appoplexia, but their brains are hard-wired for aggression. If you become one, you'll certainly become much stronger, but you'll also become a bit dimmer and more violent... Are you sure you want this?

objects.title: Arachnachimp
objects.text: Arachnachimps are aliens from Aranhascimmia. They combine the features of the monkey and spiders of your planet into a single package, featuring multiple limbs, acrobatic prowess, and the ability to make webbing.

objects.title: Cerebrocrustacean
objects.text: Cerebrocrustaceans are aliens from Encephalonus IV. Their immensely-sized brains grant them a level of intelligence that rivals that of Galvans, though they tend to be somewhat egotistical. I don't believe that becoming one will change your personality, but such vast knowledge can corrupt...

objects.title: Ectonurite
objects.text: Ectonurites are ghost-like aliens from Anur Phaetos. They can become intangible and invisible at will, but are notably weak to sunlight. They can possess other creatures as well, but that would likely be frowned upon.

objects.title: Flourana
objects.text: Florauna are plant-based aliens from Flors Verdance. They're typically savage and tribal by nature, but it's not unheard of for members of the species to integrate into more advanced civilizations. They possess a number of plant-based abilities such as chlorokinesis and regeneration.

objects.title: Galvan
objects.text: The Galvans from Galvan Prime are among the brightest minds in my universe, the creators of the Omnitrix and Neotrix being counted among their number. Despite standing at around a half a foot tall, they're naturally brilliant and technologically gifted. They're also remarkably long lived.

objects.title: Gimlinopithecus
objects.text: Gimlinopithecus are yeti-like aliens from Pattersonea. They are capable of generating large amounts of electricity and controlling it through electrokinesis. They can also telekinetically control objects by charging them with their electricty.

objects.title: Gourmand
objects.text: Gourmands are short aliens from Peptos XII. They were originally from Peptos I, but they foolishly consumed it and ten other planets in order to save it from invasion. They're also divided into two subspecies, the Perks and the Murks. I'll let you choose which you'll be.

objects.title: Incursean
objects.text: Incurseans are a war-loving species of aliens that rule over a large portion of space in my universe, though Plumber activity has reduced their hold in recent years. Even so, becoming one would be an... unusual choice. It would certainly make you stand out among the other new recruits.

objects.title: Kineceleran
objects.text: Kinecelerans are aliens from the planet Kinet. They're very fast, having the ability to run at speeds of 500 miles per hour. They can easily run on water or walls and can stop on a dime. Quite impressive.

objects.title: Kraaho
objects.text: Kraaho are tungsten-based aliens from an incredibly hot planet. They're incredibly resilient to extreme heat as a result, but Earth's temperature is notably frigid to them. Their bodies can also stretch as if made of an elastic material.

objects.title: Lenopan
objects.text: Lenopans are a species of aliens that, in their most natural form, appear to be made of purple mud. They are capable of shapeshifting, however, and can easily take the the form of a human or even an object. They were originally enemies of the Plumbers but, after decades of diplomacy, have become staunch allies.

objects.title: Lepidopterran
objects.text: Lepidopterrans are insectoid aliens from Lepidopterra. They can produce green slime from their eyestalks and naturally produce a... rather nasty odor. Sorry, but it truly is unpleasant. They can fly and have a number of other abilities, but is it worth it? I'm not so certain.

objects.title: Loboan
objects.text: Loboans are aliens from Luna Lobo, the moon of Anur Transyl. They're wolf-like and possess many of the traits of the lupine creatures from your planet. They can also amplify their howls and possess enhanced strength and durability.

objects.title: Mechamorph
objects.text: Galvanic Mechamorphs are technological beings originating from Galvan Prime's moon, Galvan B. They posses the ability to enhance most technological machines temporarily by merging with them. As they're composed of nanites, they can also freely change shape, though not to the extent of Lenopans.

objects.title: Merlinisapien
objects.text: Merlinosapiens are aliens with chameleon-like abilities. Their most notable ability is a form of camouflage that borders on invisibility, but this ability does have weaknesses. They're also exceptionally agile, quick, and flexible.

objects.title: Methanosian
objects.text: Methanosians are plant-like aliens from Methanos. They possess chlorokinesis and can generate flame from their palms in flamethrower-like blasts. They do have a noticeably bad scent, however, and their chlorokinesis pales in comparison to that of Flouranas.

objects.title: Necrofriggian
objects.text: Necrofriggians are insectoid aliens native to Kylmyys. They breed asexually and, when the time comes, have a compulsive need to gather metal to form a nest. This urge will come over you once the time comes. Oh, and they possess cryokinesis and flight. I suppose I should mention that as well.

objects.title: Petrosapian
objects.text: Petrosapians are silicon-based aliens from the planet of Petropia. Being crystalline in nature, they're remarkably durable and possess regenerative properties. They can also fire crystal shards from their body, making them excellent defensive and offensive combatants.

objects.title: Piscciss Volann
objects.text: Piscciss Volanns are, as their name suggests, aliens from the planet Piscciss. They're exceptionally powerful underwater combatants, being able to breathe underwater and withstand immense pressure. That being said, they can't stay on land for very long and are weak to fire. I'd be surprised if you chose this.

objects.title: Planchakle
objects.text: Planchakles are aliens from Aul-Turrhen. They're small but bright aliens with incredibly ingenuitive streaks that make for wonderful mechanics and builders. That being said, they tend to rebuild things to suit their needs rather than for practicality, making them unusual.

objects.title: Pyronite
objects.text: Pyronites are plasma-based lifeforms from the star Pyros. They have the power of pyrokinesis and can generate massive flames. They're also able to fly and absorb flames, allowing them to put out flames just as fast as they can start them.

objects.title: Pyronite
objects.text: Tetramands are a four-armed warrior species from the planet Khoros. They notably have a matriarchal society due to the fact that females of their species are stronger than the males. According to their traditions, if a male bests a female in combat, he is to become her husband.

objects.title: Uxorites
objects.text: Uxorites are aliens from Ringa Morr. They possess powerful telekinetic abilities and the ability to fly, likely as a result of using those powers on themselves. Their psychic powers and enhanced reflexes come from the combined strength of three brains working in tandem, so I've heard.

objects.title: Vaxasaurian
objects.text: Vaxasaurians are aliens from Terradino. They're fairy strong and durable, but their main power lies in their ability to grow or shrink through dimensional displacement. Even when reduced in size, however, they're very large. Incredibly so. At minimum, they can become about 10 feet tall.

objects.title: Vulpimancer
objects.text: Vulpimancers are an animalistic species from the planet Vulpin. I'm... honestly not sure why you'd choose this, or even why we offer it. They do have incredible senses of smell and hearing, but they can't see at all and their language is far too complex for universal translators to translate... Still, it is an option.

rows.title: #trix Options
rows.titleText: "The #trix is, as its name suggests, an upgraded version of the Omnitrix. While the original device was crafted by a genius by the name of Azmuth, the subsequent devices were made by his daughter, Volta. Unlike the original, they are not locked to a single key DNA signature, meaning that you will not be forced to appear as a Tennyson clone while in human form. This being said, it will be bonded to your DNA, preventing others from removing it without highly advanced technology. "Like the original Omnitrix, the #trix's primary function is to allow its user to transform into one of many alien forms temporarily. Each #trix is also equipped with holographic displays and an inbuilt AI to assist in its use. An #trix is designed to be far more user friendly than the original model, though certain features, like Master Control, are still locked for user safety until Volta approves their usage. "You can customize your #trix in a great deal many ways, from choosing how it's designed physically to selecting what features it has. If you perform your duties well, you may be permitted to upgrade your #trix in the future, but at first, you will be restricted to a certain amount of 'points' to keep your device balanced and safe."

rows.title: Your Fate
rows.titleText: Now, let's discuss your fate. There are, of course, many things I can't decide. Who you will be and what you will do is wholly up to you, and the events that unfold are up to chance. Yes, I know some things, but I'm not permitted to say what they are just yet. I can, however, help guide you by determining several key pieces of your fate.

objects.title: Reincarnation
objects.text: You'll be reborn as a native inhabitant of the universe. In most cases, this will place you on the setting's equivalent of Earth or the most significant planet. The benefits to this are that you'll receive a proper education in the world and identification qualifying you as a citizen. The downside is that you'll need to wait until you're older to receive your Neotrix, which will be securely sent to you when you turn 10.

objects.title: Drop-In
objects.text: Alternatively, you can be placed in the world as you are, with your physical options chosen and your Neotrix in hand. This option 'gets you in the action' quickly, so to speak, but it also results in you sticking out like a sore thumb. In some universes, this may not be a problem, but in others, it likely will be.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
